cafes.name: PHX Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 147 E Garfield St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA

text.text: I love the phoenix cat cafe!! My girlfriend and I have been twice and have felt so welcomed every time we came in! All of the cats there are so sweet and special and fun in their own ways:) It‚Äôs kept so clean in the lobby and they make amazing coffee that you definitely have to try when you are there! The workers are so so kind and will chat with you for 20 minutes about the cats if you want to which is pretty awesome! Definitely recommend going here and we will be back soon!! Someone give clementine a little hug for us too:)

Paws down, this was such a wonderful experience and did my soul some much needed good.  I‚Äôm reading these nasty reviews and they are such an inaccurate portrayal of what this facility truly is.  If one actually takes the time to read the information presented on the website, in the facility, or on any of the paperwork or even their social media they states the rules clearly. As a very experienced cat owner myself this concept is wonderful. Not only do these cats get to be free of cages, playing, and clearly well cared for; It gives potential adopters the opportunity to see how they behave in less stressful environment.  Just like humans, cats have social batteries too. They have needs and their emotional well-being/needs to be taken into consideration which is EXACTLY what they are doing at Phoenix Cat Cafe.  Every single person that I interacted, with was kind, knowledgeable about each cat, and professional.  The facility is so clean and these cats are as happy as they can be in this environment. These negative comments on here are just taking jabs at employees because they weren‚Äôt getting what they wanted which sounds more like an entitlement problem than a Phoenix Cat Cafe problem.  We had a first spot morning reservation, which we booked for 2 adults, because we read and used our comprehension skills based on the VERY CLEAR information on the website (and Instagram and when you walk in the door‚Ä¶).  We purchased coffee prior to visiting the cats, we read the posted rules, followed directions and proceeded into the cat area quiet and respectfully.  We took a seat on the floor and within seconds we were surrounded and greeted by several cats. The kind woman who was working even took the time to tell us who each cat was (mind you there were over 20) and she knew all of them.  The bonded pairs, their stories, and individual health needs.  She told us about the Manx (I love and can‚Äôt stop thinking about Clem üòª) and the cat with one eye - they were both content, loving and happy.  I love that they enforce the rules about bringing children into the facility. This isn‚Äôt a petting zoo. These are animals who have been ditched, abused, scared, and the last thing they need is to be stressed out by a bunch of kids running around in THEIR space.  I‚Äôm saying this as a parent and cat owner. I have zero bad things to say about this place and the only thing I wish I could‚Äôve done was take one of these sweet little babies home.  Mine at home are not open to this.  I love having the option of being able to have coffee with a friend and love on some furry friends in the process. Cats are far better than most people anyways.  Even if you aren‚Äôt in the market to adopt a cat, it gives you the ability to socially interact and show some cats who need some love just that. Keep doing what you‚Äôre doing Phoenix Cat Cafe - I can‚Äôt wait to visit again.  Please give Miss Clem so love for me.  (I‚Äôd love to work in the new location whenever that opens.)

We were here 2 weeks ago and had a blast! We reserved a time since availability is limited and we had a larger group. Staff was amazing, told us all about the cats, their names, personalities, the coffee was amazing.  Highly recommend! Just make sure to read all the requirements before going and use common sense!

cafes.name: Black Cat Coffee House
cafes.address: 4730 E Indian School Rd Suite 120, Phoenix, AZ 85018, USA

text.text: I went around noon on a weekday and had the whole place to myself. There were many cushioned seats available. The staff were friendly. Although they said they haven't done latte art in a while, one said she would try to make the bear for me. She did absolutely amazing, especially for a latte with almond milk instead of dairy! It turned out super cute and tasted great to match. I highly recommend checking this place out but they may not always be able to do latte art. They have some specialty coffee mixes that would be nice to try anyway
I stopped here to buy a coffee, it was not bad, 8 points from 10. Place lost its atmosphere, furniture is too old. In total not bad

Muffin was so mid, very dry. My coffee was pretty great, this just isn't a place to find a good pastry. I ended up getting something else from the Safeway in the same lot to satisfy my hunger. I ordered a bagel and Idk how only half of a bagel adds up to 9 dollars, that seems fraudulent. Service was fine,  the shop is adorable though, very cozy. Would return to this shop to try their other unique coffee options and to use the free WiFi.

cafes.name: Kitty Pause Kitty Caf√©
cafes.address: Pavilions Shopping Center, 1837 W Guadalupe Rd UNIT 107, Mesa, AZ 85202, USA

text.text: I have been here twice a year after the other, and both times I have found my forever furbabies (pics included). It is not an actual cat cafe, but it‚Äôs an hour of free play with the kitties. They have various ages of cats from kitten to adult. Most of them are always up for adoption. The adoption process was so easy, I applied the same day and picked up my cat the next day. If you have one cat and looking for another, this is the place to go! Since they‚Äôve already been around cats before, the introduction process was very quick and my cats are now definitely best friends. Only con is I don‚Äôt think I could go back because I would end up bringing home another and my boyfriend would not be too happy. Would recommend to friends and family looking for a cat.

First time at this kitty Pause and we absolutely loved it! My nieces wanted to take home every cat here! I love that they have an activity center for cat lovers to spread some love while these adorable babies are waiting to get adopted! This is such a great concept! Staff very welcoming and professional and so kind! We will definitely be back!

Brought my 10 year old crazed cat lady daughter here yesterday and she had her fill of loving more cats (She ALREADY has 3 at home). I really appreciate the rules they have and the way they communicate expectations is clear and friendly. As much as she wanted to count paws and rub her face behind the ears of these beauties, she refrained and was able to give the cats treats, love on the cats that wanted to be pet & played with them and had a great time! The cafe is very clean, organized and smells amazing. You can tell the staff really care for these cats by the amazing set up, the care and the atmosphere of the cafe. A Gentleman helped us yesterday (I think his name is Stu or Stan?) but he was great. Good job to the staff and anyone involved in making this Kitty Pause Kitty Cafe a success! *Highly Recommend*

cafes.name: El Jefe Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 3025 N Campbell Ave Suite 151, Tucson, AZ 85719, USA

text.text: Wow! This place is special, the staff is kind and laid back with best interests for the cats while giving great customer service. My 8 & 10 yo had a memorable visit. The visit for me was most enjoyable bc customers are so happy to be with the cats, it was a comfortable, clean, and epic vibe experience. Great job getting cats safe homes while serving the community.

Absolutely loved visiting all the sweet, loveable cats at El Jefe Cat Cafe!! The right side of the building is where you buy time (Hour increments), Cafe drinks, and cat treats to enjoy while you visit the cat cafe section to the left of the building. Right side also houses lots of cute merchandise for yourself and your cats! Cafe drinks were extremely delicious and well priced! Once you purchase time and whatever else, you exit and enter the left part of the building which is a cute 3- story layout with a bunch of cute, adoptable, and lovable cats. We bought treat tokens and chose Churro tube treats. Most cats were sleepy since it was later in the day but enticing them with treats, quickly most of all the cats (except for the shy ones) come to greet us and were ready to love on us. It was clean and you could tell all the cats were well cared for! I loved every second of my visit and can't wait to visit again!

Get your kittah fix! Lovely cats and kittens looking for your love and affection. Attached to a coffee shop where you can buy fun feline related gear. Good way to spend time with a cat before adopting or just because you love cats. Go!

cafes.name: Hunter's Kitten Lounge
cafes.address: 5319 E Speedway Blvd, Tucson, AZ 85712, USA

text.text:
Had a fun time with all the cats‚ù£Ô∏è
Just discovered the Kitten Lounge and booked an appt online the same morning when they opened.
There is a gift shop at the check in area with locally made items.
What a great idea Melissa had to turn this idea into reality.
There is a Bio book so you can read more about each cat.  They range from young to old.  Can adopt them.  They have classes on their schedule like kitty yoga, rock painting, movie night with cats.
Makes your heart happy‚ù£Ô∏è‚ù£Ô∏è
It was worth the money and if you can add a donation to help that would be even better.

I was excited to try this cat lounge with my two daughters. It‚Äôs a really lovely space and I can tell the cats seem settled there and content. There was no swiping like I‚Äôve seen at other cat cafes. The staff seems very hands on and attentive to the cats and the space and the guests. They gave us treats to feed the cats at no extra charge. There are plenty of seating options, games, tables, books. It was a cozy environment and of course the cats are super cute and fun to hang with. This guy was my 10 year old‚Äôs favorite- she made me take a picture of it ;)

My husband and I loved this place. The workers were so friendly and it was well kept. All the kitties seemed loved and taken care of and it was the best time petting and cuddling them. Thank you for all you do SACR and Hunters Kitten Lounge!
